      "writtenOn": "2020-02-19T17:41:45Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Can we define the \"digest counter by test\" and the expectations.Expectations inside this test?\n\nRationale:\n- The reader needs to think about the expectedDeltas, the \"digest counter by test\" and the expectations to make sense of this test.\n- These data are tricky because \"untriaged\" could mean a digest with no associated expectation, or a digest with an expectation labeled \"untriaged\". Let\u0027s make it as simple as possible for the reader to clearly see all these nuances.\n- Luckily these things are small enough that we can define them within the test.\n\nBonus points if the inputs include a digest that is untriaged by virtue of not having a corresponding entry in the expectations (as opposed to being explicitly labeled as untriaged).",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 75,
        "startChar": 37,
        "endLine": 75,
        "endChar": 107
      },
